{
  "name": "shared-skill-bundle-targets",
  "createdAt": "2026-04-29T11:00:09.785Z",
  "description": "Adds first-class shared file support for skill bundles so plugin installers can route shared templates to a dedicated shared directory while preserving compatibility when no shared target is configured. Agent plugin installers now install and uninstall only specd-managed skills, keeping unrelated user skills untouched during full uninstall operations. The change also standardizes shared template references and verifies end-to-end behavior across codex, claude, copilot, and opencode plugin workflows.",
